product_name: Charlotte TilburyUnreal Skin Sheer Glow Tint Hydrating Foundation Stick
summary: SummaryCharlotte Tilbury Unreal Skin Sheer Glow Tint Hydrating Foundation Stick is light coverage hydrating foundation stick in 20 flexible shades that glides and blends for a weightless second-skin finish glow.
details: DetailsFeaturesSwipe, Blend And Glow! A super-natural foundation that instantly smooths, blurs and leaves a soft-focus finish. Packed with Hyaluronic Acid, Vitamin E and Collageneer, it immediately hydrates and nourishes for more youthful-looking skin. Available in 20 stretchable shades.Key IngredientsMulti-Molecular Weight HA Blend - Gives the skin a plumper appearance and nourishes the skinVitamin E - Transforms dull complexions with antioxidant and moisturizing abilitiesDaikon Radish Seed Oil - Moisturizes, helps skin to feel smoother and firmer over timeResearch ResultsIn a clinical test on 33 people, immediately after one application, results showed:Moisturizes and keeps hydration locked in for up to 24 hoursSkin looks smoother and plumper and feels firmerSkin looks 32 times smootherItem 2625903How To UseLightly glide on and blend from the center of the face outwards. Blend it with your fingers for sheer coverage or with a complexion brush for buildable, weightless coverage.Wear your perfect unreal shade match for a super-natural glowing skin finish.Apply over existing makeup as a touch up on the go for an instant soft glow effect.Ingredients1 Fair: C15-19 Alkane, Octyldodecanol, Tridecyl Trimellitate, Mica, Pentaerythrityl Tetraisostearate, Polyethylene, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Sucrose Tetrastearate Triacetate, Raphanus Sativus (Radish) Seed Extract, Cera Microcristallina/Microcrystalline Wax/Cire Microcristalline, Silica, Silica Silylate, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil, Tocopheryl Acetate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Hydrolyzed Sodium Hyaluronate, Lupinus Albus Seed Extract, Dicalcium Phosphate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Rosmarinus Officinalis (Rosemary) Leaf Extract, Tocopherol, Tin Oxide. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments:
I received this in exchange for my honest review. Charlotte Tilbury has done it again! The Unreal Skin Foundation Stick is everything I hoped for and more. It glides on like silk, blends seamlessly, and leaves my skin looking smooth, even, and radiant—like my skin, but better.

It's perfect for those days when you want a natural, fresh-faced look. The coverage is buildable: light for everyday wear but easy to layer if you need more. It doesn't cake, crease, or cling to dry patches (which is rare for a stick formula), and the finish is that signature CT healthy glow—never greasy, just luminous.

What I really appreciate is how portable and mess-free it is. It's become my go-to for touch-ups or travel, and the formula wears beautifully throughout the day. Also, bonus points for being hydrating—it doesn't leave my skin feeling tight or dry.

If you love products that are easy to use, flattering on the skin, and give that effortless "glow from within" finish, this one's a must-try. Charlotte nailed it!

reviews.headline: Best foundation I've ever used
reviews.comments: Hands down the best finish I've ever gotten from a foundation. Glowy without looking greasy, and a light layer looks so natural it's impossible to tell you're even wearing it. The only indication is the hydrating effect you can feel on your skin. The self-contained stick makes for the most efficient and mess-free application. It blends almost effortlessly. I really can't say enough good things about this product. I've been using it for about 5 weeks and can confirm that it is totally worth the price point. When I eventually run out I will most likely be a repeat customer. I love Charlotte Tilbury. In their case the price truly reflects the quality—check out their matte lipsticks!!

media.headline: Good product but not for me

faceoff_positive.comments:
I received this product for free, BUT I'm going to give you an honest review. The product is ok.  I'm not "obsessed" the way so many others seem to be. 

This formula is GREAT for the winter time but will just leave you feeling greasy in the summer...and this is coming from someone with combo skin that leans dry. The color I received was a bit darker than my actual color, but since it's pretty sheer, blending it out just made me look like I've been in the sun for a few hours which is why I mentioned this would be great for the winter. It's hydrating so you really don't need to pile on extra skin care products underneath. If you do, you will just cause a mess. A little serum and your primer and you're good to go. The finish gives you a dewy glow, but if you tend to run oily, that dewy glow will turn into slick mess, especially during a hot day which is why, again, I recommend this more for cooler temperatures. If you're oily, I recommend setting with a powder. Maybe powder and spray. I wouldn't set with just a spray. In my opinion, the formula doesn't really dry down enough in hotter temperatures when sweating is a thing to worry about.

Coverage: as noted, it is sheer so this is for the girlies and the bois that just want a touch of something to give them a healthy complexion. The formula is buildable, but only to a certain extent. Again, the point of this product is to be sheer. I like that it's in stick form so if you need to touch up, that's an easy fix. If you have a problem with blemishes, don't bother with this product. The coverage isn't enough to even you out.

Would I buy it? Possibly, but with the coverage being so light, I could only use it occasionally because unfortunately, I'm not blessed to have picture perfect skin. Would I recommend for those with nice skin? Sure. Everybody could use a little pick me up and I think this product is good for those days where you just want to feel a little put together. Nothing over the top...just a healthy glow
faceoff_positive.headline: Great hydration, sheer coverage

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received this foundation stick complimentary in exchange for my honest opinion. The packaging is lovely, and I'm under the impression that it's refillable as I was able to pull the entire gold tube straight out without much effort, but I don't see refills sold anywhere.

Stick formulas tend to feel heavy, and on first application, this one feels suffocating until you sheer it out with a brush. It is moisturizing over my combination skin, but it might be too much for those with oily skin as it was borderline uncomfortable for me. This is billed as a light coverage foundation that is buildable, but that is pretty much impossible to do considering how thick it feels.

Glow wise, it does a nice job of giving that dewy, almost sweaty, look without being too glittery. The issue is more that it is not flattering for those with more mature skin or for those who don't already have good skin to begin with. And again, buildable coverage is not practical because this stick will give you an almost metallic, robot look if you don't sheer it out.

This would best be applied as a stick highlighter rather than as a foundation. The ideal demographic for this product as it was meant to be used is probably someone in their 20s and not me. 😅
